I'm glad to hear your endeavors to improve your Matter Sorc are coming along well. I'm glad to hear that you'll be one of five or so Sorcs worth a flip in PvP. You've succesfully denied the requests of the other 99% of the class you TL, in improving our limitted CC and RvR capabilities. <P>You claim that you've seen what the Matter Sorc can be in PvP, well I played RZ (pvp server) since EQ went gold. I came to DAoC knowing what mez is worth and knowing which class I wanted to play. Now, having been billed as the premier cc class, watch Mid healers prove what I already knew. <P>Building my Sorc has been a total fight, the whole way. I fully expected a challenge, in exchange of going into RvR as "the" CC class. <P>You have been combative, with anyone that does not agree with your line of thinking. You have gone out of your way to manufactor strategies that are untested and non functional, to explain why our CC is watered down. How about saying "Ayap, we aren't good CC'rs, and we definitely aren't great soloists", instead of arguing blindly against this.<P>You say we are the "vocal minority". Not even. Many voices have spoken here, but ... how many Sorcs are there really? Couple this with the fact that the voices here are a statistical sampling of a "majority" and really do represent what Sorcs think. Do you REALLY believe that with all the objection posted here, there's really 5,000 other Sorcs out there that believe entirely opposite of us?<P>The class you were CHOSEN to represent consists of 97% mind/body based Sorcs. You want to represent the majority, prove it. Every class has a spec that gets left behind. For Armsmen, it's usually parry, since two hand or polearm and slash/thrust take all the points. Now, you could max Parry and gimp your weapon.... I think not. Matter spec has DoT and debuff, Mind has mem blur and charm, Body has nuke and debuff, seems pretty even to me. <P>You can claim what you want, but you are NOT addressing our needs. You are NOT representing the class, and from where I stand it looks a lot like you are using your position to serve your own intrests.<P>Don't take this as a personal attack, it's only one Sorc's perspective, although perhaps shared by many. <P>btw, what's your highest level Sorc's name, lvl and server now (last I heard was 21ish, but I'm sure you're higher now).<P>Dop
